<Frontiers41DeBr> <On 22nd June 1941, our offensive against Stalin's Soviet Union will begin! Our forces, together with our allies from Finland, Rumania, Slovakia and Hungary, will attack along the entire Soviet western border. As a part of Luftflotte 2, our first task is to secure air supremacy in area around Lemberg. According to intelligence reports, much of the Soviet air force is concentrated on forward air fields. Our first task will be to put the Soviet planes out of action, preferably on the ground, then we will directly support our advancing armoured spearheads of Heeresgruppe Mitte. With luck, we will be in Moscow in a few months!>
<Frontiers41DeDb> <The German attack was totally successful. Heeresgruppe Mitte took Lemberg after a few days. Luftflotte 2 was instrumental in this success. As on other parts of the front, the total of destroyed enemy planes is almost incredible, several thousands on the ground alone. The fighter units also maintained air cover above our troops by shooting down hundreds of attacking Soviet bombers. Our troops continue to advance deeper and deeper into Soviet territory. The Soviet resistance in the air has almost ceased, while on the ground numerous, but ill trained and equipped Soviet troops offer heavy resistance. The Luftwaffe is the decisive force in this ground war and we have to keep up our efforts to keep the pace of our advance.>
<Frontiers41RuBr> <As a part of 15 SAD of the Kiev Special Military District, our unit is based on a forward airfield in the area of Lvov in the western Ukraine. There have been no orders from our commanders, but there are reports that strong German forces have crossed the border and have already captured part of Pshemisl. We are under strict orders not to engage in any activity that could be interpreted as hostile by a clique of revisionist German generals who want to provoke Hitler into a war with us, though our aircraft have been fuelled.>
<Frontiers41RuDb> <On the morning of June 22nd, the German forces attacked. The attack came as a total surprise and resulted in heavy losses. Lvov was lost after several days of fighting to the Germans, who were assisted by anti-Soviet Ukrainian nationalists. They committed many atrocities there and everywhere else. The VVS took extremely heavy losses, mainly on the ground due to surprise attacks. In the air, the VVS fought bravely and made the Germans pay a heavy price for their aggression.>
