<Rzhev41DeBr> <After the Vyazma encirclement of mid-October the Russians in front of our forces amounted to a few reserve formations.   The only fighting since has been a fierce battle at Borodino, where the enemy threw in his last fresh troops, for propaganda purposes.  Elsewhere, our troops struggle forward against the mud.  The advance may have to be stopped for the ground to freeze, and then resumed, with only a few flying days before the winter snows.>
<Rzhev41DeDb> <Though our forces attempted an attack from the north of Moscow, eventually they were forced into a direct attack on the western fortications.  Progress was slow, and our troops exhausted by the cold, leading to the abandonment of the offensive for this year.  The capture of Moscow will have to wait for the summer.>
<Rzhev41RuBr> <The first of our reinforcements from the east were destroyed in the fighting on the Borodino battlefield in mid-October.  The rain has given us time to build another line of defence in front of Moscow, though there will be a few days before the snows build up when the enemy armoured troops can operate on the frozen mud.  The government has been moved from the capital.  One more collapse and Moscow will fall to the invader.>
<Rzhev41RuDb> <Our soldiers fought hard battles at Voloklansk and Naro-Fominsk which delayed the enemy for long enough that winter set in and his armoured troops became immobilised in the snow. More reinforcements are arriving and in the new year we are to take the offensive to push the enemy out of his advanced positions near Moscow.>
