<Belgorod42DeBr> <We have defeated the Soviet winter offensive and are well placed to attack the weak forces remaining in front of us.  The first objective is Voronezh, but that is only to protect the flank of a drive towards the Soviet oil reserves in the Caucasus.  Our Hungarian and Italian allies are to supply additional forces, as much of the Wehrmacht remains to defend the salient in front of Moscow.  The enemy are exhausted and the battle should begin with another round up of their troops.>
<Belgorod42DeDb> <Though our initial attacks were successful, the penetration was too shallow because of the focus on the south, and the enemy failed to commit further troops, so our bag of prisoners was less than previous ones.  Still, Voronezh was captured easily, and held against a brief counter-attack.  The panzers that defended the city have moved to the south, leaving only the less-equipped forces of our allies to defend the west bank of the Don.>
<Belgorod42RuBr> <The winter offensive was less successful in the south than around Moscow, which got most of the reinforcements and newer equipment.  Our front is not strong enough to withstand the panzers and forces are being gathered to the rear rather than deployed in support of us.  However, every day we delay the German advance allows our factories to produce more planes, tanks and guns with which to smash the invasion.>
<Belgorod42RuDb> <Our front has collapsed, and we have lost the city of Voronezh.  While the crisis is not on the same scale as last year, unless more armies are sent to the south a vast amount of the southern Soviet Union will fall under Nazi control.  The cities of Stalino and Stalingrad owe their names to our leader's successful offensive against the Whites in this region.  We must hope that the same traps work again.>
