<Myskhako43DeBr> <General von Manstein managed to blunt the Soviet advance at Kharkov with a series of bold manoeuvre battles, stabilizing the front.  We are still holding bridgeheads over the Kuban River, since the Reich must have oil and the army will be required to resume the offensive in summer.  After the attempt to isolate Heeresgruppe Süd failed, the Red Army began a frontal attack to drive us from the Kuban and have landed forces at Myskhako to outflank the southern part of our defences at Novorossiysk.  For that reason, the major part of Luftflotte 4, including the whole of Jagdgeschwader 52, have been sent to airfields in the Kuban and Eastern Crimea. They will support the counter-offensive against the Soviet beachhead. Since the flying weather is good, we are confident that we will be able to achieve air supremacy, and it is planned to use large numbers of Stuka dive-bombers to support the assault. It is however known that the Soviet air force has moved very strong units there, equipped with planes delivered from the Americans and British.> 
<Myskhako43DeDb> <The Soviets have failed to take Novorossiysk or break through our central defences, though they managed to retain their beachhead. The extremely tough air battles that were fought over the Kuban seem to have prevented either side from achieving their objectives. The Soviet air force, especially the fighters, was very well organized, numerically superior and very aggressive. The aces of JG 3 and 52 were able to achieve a local superiority, but the Stukas were not able to operate unhindered and the Soviet flak was intense.  If we are unable to inflict greater losses on the enemy, the air war over the East front will become more and more unfavourable.>
