<Bagration44DeBr> <After the Soviet offensives in the Ukraine, Rumania is now under attack from the Soviets. The Soviets managed to push our forces back from their territory everywhere in the south. Heeresgruppe Mitte holds a huge "front balcony" extending to the Dnepr. A huge building up of Soviet forces in the vicinity suggests that the Soviets will try to take this bulge in their own 1944 summer offensive. The German forces in the bulge cannot hold it. Due to the invasion in the Normandy, much of the mobile forces have been sent westward. The Luftwaffe has the same situation: Many experienced pilots of JG 51, the only fighter unit in the area, have been transferred to the Reichsluftverteidigung. Our forces are hopelessly outnumbered.>
<Bagration44DeDb> <On the third anniversary of the attack on the Soviet Union, the Soviet offensive started to crush Heeresgruppe Mitte. Within days, over 300,000 German soldiers died or were captured. A disaster larger than Stalingrad. The Luftwaffe was too weak to render any effective resistance. Constant Il-2 attacks on our airfields kept us fighting for our very lives while entire armies died in the field. The whole central East front has collapsed and we don't know how or when we can contain the Soviet breakthrough.>
<Bagration44RuBr> <In the third year of this war, the tide has turned. Unlike in the previous years, we will be launching a summer offensive, not the Germans. On the exact anniversary of the German aggression the Red Army will execute Operation Bagration, a strike at the German occupied part of Belarus. Our aim is to crush the German front and break through into Poland, enabling us to launch attacks both on Hungary and East Prussia. The VVS will massively support this offensive, the main task will be to destroy the Luftwaffe in our sector and the support the offensive.>
<Bagration44RuDb> <Operation Bagration has been a huge success! Vitebsk was taken and our forces are still contiuing westward. In the area around Vitebsk, more German soldiers were killed or captured than at Stalingrad. The Luftwaffe was not able to put of any serious resistance and was mostly not even able to defend its own airfields from constant VVS attacks. Except for the Baltics, now all of our Motherland has been liberated from the Germans. Now we will carry the war to them!>
