<Ukraine44DeBr> <After the disaster around Smolensk and Vitebsk, the remains of Heeresgruppe Mitte are on constant retreat. A holding line has been set up around Lemberg in the southern part of the Soviet advance, but it will not hold very long. We expect the Soviet advance to turn south there and cross the Karpathian Mountains into Hungary. This move would cut off Germany from the oil fields in Rumania and Hungary. Heeresgruppe Süd will support the Royal Hungarian army in the defence of the Hungarian border. Luftflotte 6, supported by units of the RLV, will give air cover alongside the Hungarian air force.>
<Ukraine44DeDb> <Lemberg fell after a short time, and the Soviets managed to cross the Carpathians into Hungary. At least we were able to prevent the Hungarians from changing sides. While the Luftwaffe and the Hungarian air force fought well, they were simply overwhelmed by the Soviets.>
