<Leningrad43WinterDeBr> <During the last days, the sovies have started to attack the positions of our 18th army at the southern shore of the Ladogasee, near Schlüsselburg. The attack is aimed at opening a land corridor to the city. We will not be able to keep the siege if the soviets can resupply by land. Luftflotte 1 must undertake a maximum effort to support our ground forces. >
<Leningrad43WinterRuBr> <Operation Iskra, the relief offensive for Leningrad, is about to begin! The VVS on the Karelian and Leningrad front will support 2nd Shock army and 67th army in their move against the german salient near Shlisselburg. The enemy air forces are weaker than in the previous year, as the Germans have withdrawn some forces westward and the finnish have assumed a defensive posture.>
<Leningrad43WinterFiBr> <The Soviets are preparing for another offensive to relieve Leningrad. Their forces are ready to strike a German position south of Ladoga. The siege of Leningrad will be very difficult to maintain when the Russians can open a land corridor. We must support the Germans in the defense of the Schlüsselburg salient. >

