<ArdennesfLFrDb> <Well, fortunately spring has come. This 1944-45 winter has been terrible: one of the coldest in history. Under very difficult weather conditions, we had to counter a desperate but very aggressive German offensive in the Ardennes. Operation Bodenplatte has failed, and the German pilots are no longer as well trained as they used to be, but they have damned good new fighters, including jets. Furthermore, the Flak is as deadly as ever, and your squadron is exhausted. However, you still have to make more efforts, until we reach the final victory! \nBetween 1943 and 1945, the French Armée de l'Air recovered from virtually nothing to become a significant force of 150,000 men, operating about 40 squadrons of bombers, fighters, reconnaissance and transport aircraft. We do have our own share of the liberation of Europe, which would have seemed inconceivable at the end of 1942, when only a few courageous men from the FAFL were fighting together with the allied air forces. These 2 years have been critical to restore the honor of French Wings. We are proud of your participation in this achievement: you certainly made French colors shine again in the skies from Europe!>

